- **Primary branches:** `master` (development), `linux-6.y` (stable), `linux-next` (integration).
- **Release cadence:** Major releases every 8â€“10 weeks; stable updates weekly.
- **Contribution model:** Review-driven patch series via mailing lists and subsystem maintainers.

