## ğŸš€ Building from Source

```bash
# Install tooling (Debian/Ubuntu example)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install build-essential libncurses-dev bison flex libssl-dev libelf-dev dwarves bc

# Clone the canonical tree
git clone https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git
cd linux

# Configure
make menuconfig  # or oldconfig/xconfig/nconfig

# Build using every available core
make -j"$(nproc)"

# Install modules + kernel
sudo make modules_install
sudo make install
```

> ğŸ’¡ Tip: stash your `.config` in version control or use `git worktree` to juggle multiple builds.

## âœ… Contributor Workflow

1. **Sync:** `git fetch origin && git rebase origin/master`
2. **Develop:** work in topic branches; keep patches atomic.
3. **Self-review:**
   ```bash
   ./scripts/checkpatch.pl --strict path/to/patch.patch
   make -j"$(nproc)" W=1
   make clang-analyzer
   ```
4. **Submit:** `git send-email` to the right subsystem mailing list + maintainers (see `MAINTAINERS`).
5. **Follow up:** track review threads on lore.kernel.org and reply with v2/v3 as needed.

## ğŸ§­ Directory Cheat Sheet

| Path | Highlights |
| --- | --- |
| `arch/` | Architecture ports (x86, arm64, riscv, â€¦) |
| `drivers/` | Device drivers grouped by subsystem |
| `include/` | Kernel + UAPI headers (`uapi/` â‡’ user space ABI) |
| `kernel/` | Scheduler, locking, timekeeping, cgroups |
| `tools/` | `perf`, `bpftool`, `spi-tools`, testing harnesses |
| `Documentation/` | Canonical manuals, guides, process docs |

## ğŸ›¡ï¸ Testing Matrix

- **KernelCI:** automated boot tests spanning architectures.
- **syzbot (syzkaller):** continuous fuzzing of kernel interfaces.
- **kselftest:** in-tree validation (`make kselftest`).
- **LTP:** Linux Test Project for ABI and syscall conformance.

## ğŸ¤ Community Resources

- **Docs:** [docs.kernel.org](https://docs.kernel.org/)
- **Patchwork tracker:** [patchwork.kernel.org](https://patchwork.kernel.org/)
- **Bugzilla:** [bugzilla.kernel.org](https://bugzilla.kernel.org/)
- **Events:** Kernel Summit, Maintainers Summit, Linux Plumbers Conference.

